div.div: I notice animation implemented by [ add ]**[ remove ] css class (that contains { transition } property), will fail to work most of the time, in one direction.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 16px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 259px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;
div.div: By thinking slowly, carefully and hard through many possiblity, I found the bug was because If I set apply a new class before a previous transition (animation) finished, the later class will fail to have animation. Solution is reduce the animation time so it wont be at the same point that second class is added.
